author: brian
msg: Changed strcpy's to use strncpy for security reasons.  Also upped
SMALLBUF to 256, which is the URL length that HTTP applications
are supposed to support.  Longterm, strncpy should be removed and
pool-based memory management used, and SMALLBUF should disappear.

author: brian
msg: Fixes a core dump caused by failing to catch the lack of a properly-set
HTTP error code in CGI responses.  Sets those to "500".
